    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s005",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 1,
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "Buda-Pesth seems a wonderful place, from the glimpse which Igot of it from the train and the little I could walk through thestreets.",
      "start_ms": 15220,
      "end_ms": 24220,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s006",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 1,
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "I feared to go very far from the station, as we had arrivedlate and would start as near the correct time as possible.",
      "start_ms": 24440,
      "end_ms": 33440,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s007",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 1,
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "Theimpression I had was that we were leaving the West and entering theEast; the most western of splendid bridges over the Danube, which ishere of noble width and depth, took us among the traditions of Turkishrule.",
      "start_ms": 33660,
      "end_ms": 42660,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s008",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 2,
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "We left in pretty good time, and came after nightfall to Klausenburgh.Here I stopped for the night at the Hotel Royale.",
      "start_ms": 42880,
      "end_ms": 51880,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s009",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 2,
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "I had for dinner, orrather supper, a chicken done up some way with red pepper, which wasvery good but thirsty.",
      "start_ms": 52100,
      "end_ms": 60500,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s010",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 2,
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "(_Mem._, get recipe for Mina.) I asked thewaiter, and he said it was called “paprika hendl,” and that, as it was anational dish, I should be able to get it anywhere along theCarpathians.",
      "start_ms": 60720,
      "end_ms": 69720,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s011",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 2,
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "I found my smattering of German very useful here; indeed, Idon’t know how I should be able to get on without it.",
      "start_ms": 69940,
      "end_ms": 78940,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s012",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 3,
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "Having had some time at my disposal when in London, I had visited theBritish Museum, and made search among the books and maps in the libraryregarding Transylvania; it had struck me that some foreknowledge of thecountry could hardly fail to have some importance in dealing with anobleman of that country.",
      "start_ms": 79160,
      "end_ms": 88160,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s013",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 3,
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "I find that the district he named is in theextreme east of the country, just on the borders of three states,Transylvania, Moldavia and Bukovina, in the midst of the Carpathianmountains; one of the wildest and least known portions of Europe.",
      "start_ms": 88380,
      "end_ms": 97380,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s014",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 3,
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "I wasnot able to light on any map or work giving the exact locality of theCastle Dracula, as there are no maps of this country as yet to comparewith our own Ordnance Survey maps; but I found that Bistritz, the posttown named by Count Dracula, is a fairly well-known place.",
      "start_ms": 97600,
      "end_ms": 106600,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s015",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 3,
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "I shall enterhere some of my notes, as they may refresh my memory when I talk over mytravels with Mina.",
      "start_ms": 106820,
      "end_ms": 115220,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
      "audio_hash": "sha256:placeholder-no-audio-generated",
      "generated_by": "internal-dry-run:kokoro:en",
      "review_status": "HOLD_HUMAN_SYNC_REVIEW_REQUIRED",
      "public": false
    },
    {
      "text_fragment_id": "dracula-chapter-001-s016",
      "chapter_id": "chapter-001",
      "paragraph_index": 4,
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "In the population of Transylvania there are four distinct nationalities:Saxons in the South, and mixed with them the Wallachs, who are thedescendants of the Dacians; Magyars in the West, and Szekelys in theEast and North.",
      "start_ms": 115440,
      "end_ms": 124440,
      "confidence": 0.72,
      "sync_level": "sentence",
      "source_hash": "f4f569c1a5486a552c3bffaaa65ecb0828a3585cccd3d702dee6dd7be00394d7",
